				<textElement textAlignment="Left" markup="html">
					<font isBold="false"/>
				</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[<b>14.</b> The Borrower hereby authorizes the Company and acknowledges its rights with respect to the
following acts:]]></text>
			</staticText>
			<staticText>
				<reportElement x="50" y="389" width="477" height="405" uuid="13b6fb81-3a97-4301-8465-4e4494fe9e92"/>
				<textElement textAlignment="Justified" markup="html"/>
				<text><![CDATA[a. To create a charge and security of the Borrowerâ€™s right, title and interest in such of the assets of the Borrower as the Company may deem fit and proper and for this purpose to execute such documents for and on behalf of the Borrower and pay all the necessary stamp duty and penalties (if any) to the government and to do all such acts, deeds and things, including approaching all the necessary authorities and/or persons, whether government, semi- government or otherwise, as may be required in this regard.<br><br>
b. To sign further MOUs, agreements, sale deeds, deeds of transfer, deeds of modification/confirmation, share transfer forms and other documents for and on behalf of the Borrower to enforce the security in the event of default by Borrower and complete the sale without any specific orders and decrees.<br><br>
c. To do all other deeds, matters and things incidental to and connected with the creation of the security for the Loan as the Company may consider necessary.<br><br>
d. To obtain re-finance against the Loan as it may consider appropriate.<br><br>
e. To enter the School / Business Premises for which the Loan has been utilized, inspect and supervise it and also inspect its books of accounts, registers and other records / documents maintained by the Borrower/s or their authorized representatives.<br><br>
f. To cancel the undrawn / unavailed / unused portion of the Loan at any time during the subsistence of the Loan, without any further notice to the Borrower, for any reason whatsoever (either regulatory or otherwise).<br><br>
g. At any time during the tenure of the Loan Agreement to revise / reschedule the repayment terms / amount of EMI or of any other amounts outstanding thereunder and the Borrower shall make all uture repayments to the Company according to such revised schedule on being notified by the Company of such revision or re -schedule.<br><br>
h. Any delay or omission by the Company in exercising any of its rights, powers or remedies as the lender of the Loan under the Loan Agreement and other documents pursuant thereto shall not impair the right, power or remedy or be construed as its waiver or acquiesce by the Company.]]></text>
